I wouldn't call this exceptional, but it is delicious and satisfying. It's simple enough for a weeknight, or for a novice cook to come across as highly skilled. My teenagers can put this together without any help from me. It's also special enough for company, and easy to multiply for a crowd without being any more time- consuming. I cooked 12 trout for my husband's birthday celebration, and enjoyed the party with our friends vs. spending the whole evening in the kitchen. Don't bake the cilantro in the oven, though. Just sprinkle it on fresh right before serving.

