Rating: 4
This is an exceptional dish that is full of flavor and is healthy at the same time. I made it 3 times already with 2 different kinds of fish, both with fantastic results! Used locally available fresh mushrooms such as shimeji, shiitake and white button for contrast in flavor and texture. Used a Chinese soy sauce for seafood but also tried it with a light soy sauce with good results. Sprinkled with toasted sesame seeds and drops of sesame oil for fragance before serving. Whisked together some soy sauce, a little sesame oil and a pinch of sesame seeds and served on the side as dipping sauce.

